sqa_test_a3439568e6a9f358047934518196ca1.new_answer: The "Nirbhaya case" refers to the gang rape and murder of a 23-year-old paramedical student in Delhi in December 2012. The victim was accompanied by her male friend at the time of the incident. While the female victim's name was not publicly disclosed due to privacy concerns and is commonly referred to as "Nirbhaya" (meaning fearless), her male companion was also a victim of the brutal assault. However, his name was not widely publicized in the same way as the female victim's pseudonym. The options provided are all fictional names and do not correspond to the actual male victim in the case. Therefore, none of the provided options are correct.
